15/06/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stipe Mesic issued a decree Tuesday (14 June), reducing the sentence of a member of the so-called Gospic group, Stjepan Grandic, who was convicted of committing war crimes against ethnic Serb civilians in 1991. His sentence will be cut from ten years to eight years, more than half of which he has already served.
In other news, Zadar Hrvatski List editor-in-chief Ivica Marijacic and former Croatian intelligence officer Markica Rebic appeared before The Hague tribunal on Tuesday. They pleaded not guilty to contempt of court charges, stemming from the publication of the name of a protected witness. (Vecernji list - 15/06/05; HRT, B92, World Bank Web site - 14/06/05) 
